<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="212" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.911/31</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>While the Department feels that it should not initiate a request for the
                            pardon of Maza, you are authorized to say to the Cuban Government that
                            the Department feels that the more than twenty months served by Maza
                            might well be considered by the Cuban Government as a sufficient
                            satisfaction of his sentence and that the United States will feel no
                            pleasure at his further confinement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>